How do I make a keyboard shortcut in CentOS 7
----------------------------------------------

Appplications/System Tools/Settings/Devices/Keyboard/Keyboard Shortcuts
Scroll down the v-scroll bar until “Custom Shortcuts” section appears
Then, click “+” icon
Fill in the "Name" text box:  Terminator
Fill in the "Command" text box: terminator --geometry=1280x800
Shortcut: click on the "set shorcut button" and hit "Super + T" keys
Click “Add” button
Close window by pressing “X” mark on top right

